===Etymology===
From Latin ''corona'', wreath.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A reward of victory or a mark of honor.
# A royal/imperial/princely headdress, [[diadem]] AND ALSO a representation of such object, as in heraldry [it may even be that only the image exists, no physical crown, as in the case of the kingdom of Belgium; by analogy such crowns can be awarded to moral persons that don't even have a head, as the mural crown for cities in heraldry].
# The top-most, highest part ''(of the head, hill, etc).''
# A wreath or band for the head.
# Imperial or regal power.
# Splendor, finish, culmination.
#: '''''crown''' achievement''
# Currency (originally) issued by the crown (5), [[koruna]], [[krona]], [[krone]].
#:''British coin - worth five [[shillings]], one quarter of a [[pound sterling]]''
# Part of a plant where root and stem meet.

